# SPA fallback for Expo Router. With web.output: "static" every route is
# pre-rendered to its own .html at export. Netlify serves an existing file
# before applying redirect rules (this rule has no "!" force flag), so
# pre-rendered pages — e.g. /vocal-range-test — are served directly; this
# catch-all only covers paths WITHOUT a matching file (client-only deep
# links / refreshes into the SPA app shell). 200 = rewrite, not redirect.
#
# POST-DEPLOY VERIFICATION (load-bearing for SEO): confirm the catch-all is
# not shadowing pre-rendered HTML —
#   curl -s https://vocalhabit.com/vocal-range-test | grep -o "<h1[^>]*>[^<]*"
# must return the page's real <h1> (and the FAQ/body text), NOT the empty app
# shell. If it returns the shell, add an explicit file-serving rule for the
# marketing routes above this line. See seo/static-rendering-architecture.md.
# Insurance: serve pre-rendered marketing pages explicitly, above the catch-all,
# so they can never be shadowed regardless of Netlify's file-precedence behavior.
# Add a line here for each new (marketing) route.
/vocal-range-test    /vocal-range-test.html    200
/*                   /index.html               200
